title: Prime Minister Research Fellowship (PMRF)
description: The Prime Minister Research Fellowship is awarded to students to promote the research trend. This means that the PMRF program is for PhD-level research in the fields of Science, Technology, Engineering, Agriculture, and Medicine. It is a collaborative effort between the Science and Engineering Research Board (SERB) and the Confederation of Indian Industry (CII). Students enrolled in Ph.D. programs at a PMRF-eligible institute benefit from this. The PMRF scheme offers Ph.D. students scholarships of up to INR 10.92 lakhs per year, with the government providing 50% and a sponsoring industry providing the remaining 50% for four years.
